originalText.text: I came to Dr. Nan Yi Chun with plantar fasciitis and gut issues. It's my first experience with accupuncture and it has been so impactful! Not only are both my issues resolved, I leave my appointments feeling renewed. Happily recommending!

originalText.text: Nan Yi is a magician! You walk into her session stressed out and leave fully relaxed. She transforms your energy and grounds you. Beyond grateful to have found her practice!

originalText.text: I sought acupuncture to help with headaches and neck pain, and I’m so happy I found Dr. Nan Yi Chun. After consistent treatments, I’m experiencing a reduction in both. Dr. Nan is kind, funny, and caring, and I always leave her office feeling so relaxed. I can’t recommend her enough!

originalText.text: I came to see Nan Yi Chun after experiencing three early miscarriages. I’m now pregnant again and for the first time, things have progressed past the first trimester and everything is looking great! I can’t recommend her enough. She’s been extremely caring and supportive through this challenging time. I was nervous to try acupuncture and I’m so happy I found her! I look forward to my weekly sessions and will continue to see her throughout the pregnancy.

originalText.text: Nan Yi is truly an expert in acupuncture. My sessions with her were calming and welcoming. I was looking for an acupuncturist that was experienced in fertility for my egg retrieval cycle. My final count was higher than expected with the help of Nan Yi and acupuncture. Nan Yi is patient and kind and takes the time to get to know her patients and understand their needs. I highly recommend Nan Yi for all your acupuncture needs- she's the best.
